\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Introduction\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Type 2 diabetes mellitus (T2DM) represents one of the most prevalent chronic diseases worldwide, affecting more than 460 million individuals and imposing a substantial burden on healthcare systems. The disease is characterized by insulin resistance and progressive \uc0\u946 -cell dysfunction, leading to chronic hyperglycemia and an increased risk of cardiovascular disease, nephropathy, neuropathy, and retinopathy.\
Lifestyle modification, including dietary intervention, remains a cornerstone of T2DM management. While pharmacological therapies are essential, diet has a profound impact on glycemic control and long-term outcomes. Traditional diabetic diets often emphasize calorie restriction and carbohydrate control; however, emerging evidence suggests that dietary patterns may be more important than macronutrient composition alone.\
The Mediterranean diet, characterized by high consumption of fruits, vegetables, whole grains, legumes, olive oil, and moderate intake of fish and poultry, has been associated with reduced cardiovascular risk and improved metabolic health. Observational studies suggest benefits for glycemic control, yet randomized controlled trials assessing its direct impact on patients with established T2DM remain limited.\
This study aims to evaluate the effects of a Mediterranean diet on glycemic control and metabolic parameters in adults with T2DM over a 24-week period.\
