\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Results\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 Baseline Characteristics\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Of the 120 participants, 112 completed the study (Mediterranean group: n = 56; control group: n = 56). Baseline characteristics, including age, sex distribution, duration of diabetes, HbA1c, BMI, and lipid profile, were comparable between groups.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Primary Outcome\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 At 24 weeks, the Mediterranean diet group demonstrated a significant reduction in HbA1c (baseline: 8.2% \'b1 0.6; 24 weeks: 7.0% \'b1 0.5), corresponding to a mean decrease of 1.2%. In contrast, the control group showed a reduction of 0.5% (p < 0.001 between groups).\
